I bow to thee (Chaitanya, as Krishna incarnate). Who can fathom the depths of
thy heart? As the juggler makes the wooden puppet dance, while it knows not
what it plays or what it sings, so, too, does the man whom you inspire, dance
without knowing why he is dancing or through whom.
